                            <comment id="17462224" author="sergey nuyanzin" created="Sun, 19 Dec 2021 15:54:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After creation of the ticket I&apos;ve noticed a PR &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/18149&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/18149&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17462433" author="martijnvisser" created="Mon, 20 Dec 2021 07:49:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for noticing that &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Sergey+Nuyanzin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Sergey Nuyanzin&quot;&gt;Sergey Nuyanzin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17463346" author="knaufk" created="Tue, 21 Dec 2021 16:32:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;master: fef7f46c476875bd2974e5303f7ae0fb9bf2faf4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Waiting for a CI for the backports to 1.14/1.13/1.12. The community currently supports Flink 1.14 and Flink 1.13 with bug fixes. I included Flink 1.12 as well, because these Log4J vulnerabilities have caused such high waves, but not Flink 1.11 because it is just a HIGH vulnerability and we have to stop somewhere. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17464409" author="JIRAUSER282522" created="Thu, 23 Dec 2021 10:06:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=knaufk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;knaufk&quot;&gt;knaufk&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are you planning to release update for version 1.11?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17464415" author="martijnvisser" created="Thu, 23 Dec 2021 10:19:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=apaC1212&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;apaC1212&quot;&gt;apaC1212&lt;/a&gt; That&apos;s not planned at the moment. The Flink community normally supports the last 3 versions, so that&apos;s 1.14, 1.13 and 1.12 right now. Because of the severity of previous CVEs, we also released additional hotfixes for older versions. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
